This paper is about knowledge graph embedding, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The proposed method, TransF, is a novel approach to embedding entities and relations in a knowledge graph, which is a common task in natural language processing and information retrieval (cs.CL) as well as database management (cs.DB). The evaluation of the proposed method involves link prediction and triple classification, which are common tasks in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses the limitations and future directions of the proposed method, which is a common practice in information retrieval and natural language processing research (cs.IR).
